        <div class="aboutinside">
              <p>↠Atal Bihari Vajpayee was born on 25 December 1924 in Gwalior's Shinde's cantonment in the state of Madhya Pradesh, India.His father's name  was Shri Krishna Bihari Vajpayee</p>
              <p>and mother's name was Krishna Devi.His early education took place in Gwalior. He graduated from Victoria College and did his MA in Political Science from DAV College , Kanpur.</p>   
              <p>Atal Bihari Vajpayee achieved a unique and commendable position while in politics. He has been the most admired Prime Minister of the country on behalf of the  Bharatiya Janata</p>
              <p>Party.He was One of the Bharat Janata Party’s(BJP) co-founders and a prominent figure.He belonged to the Rashtriya Swayamsevak Sangh, a group of volunteers with Hindu  nationalist.</p>         
              <p>views.He was the first Indian prime minister to hold office for the whole duration who was not a member of the Indian National Congress. He was also a well-known writer and poet.</p>
              <p>As India’s 10th prime minister, Atal Bihari Vajpayee was an Indian politician and diplomat who held office for three terms: for 13 days in 1996, for 13 months from 1998 to 1999,</p>
              <p>and then for a full term from 1999 to 2004.  </p>
                
       
